      "content": "i mean, when u say a \"lack of cultural fluency,\" u basically saying they wouldn't fit in because of how they talk. isn't that just a way of saying that people who don't use standard english are inherently less professional? it feels like u are saying their ability to do the job is tied to being \"white-collar\" in their speech. isn't that kind of a biased way to judge someone's actual talent?",
